The '''ICE breaker''' was a powerful [[Computer/Legends|computer]] [[Slicer/Legends|slicing]] tool, which was encoded so that it could only access a computer onboard the [[Leviathan (Interdictor-class cruiser)|''Leviathan'']]. A [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] [[Unidentified Rodian prisoner (Leviathan)|prisoner]] aboard the ''Leviathan'' traded it to a companion of [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] in exchange for his freedom from the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Warship/Legends|warship's]] detention block. If asked how it was [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggled]] into his own holding cell, the Rodian's response was to say that the [[Darth Revan's Sith Empire|Sith]] were not very thorough in their search. It was then used to free Revan, [[Bastila Shan]], [[Carth Onasi]], and the rest of the crew of the ''[[Ebon Hawk]]''.

==Behind the scenes==
"ICE" is a term coined by [[Wikipedia:William Gibson|William Gibson]] in the 1984 cyberpunk novel [[Wikipedia:Neuromancer|''Neuromancer'']]. Standing for Intrusion Countermeasures Electronics, it was an early concept of an antivirus program or firewall. Hackers attempted to defeat ICE with programs called "icebreakers."

